# ✅ **Issues for Graphical Client Display (R-Type)**

---

### **1. Title:** Implement window creation & main render loop

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Set up the graphical window and the continuous refresh loop.
**List the actions required.:**

Create the client window
Set up the rendering loop with proper framerate control
Handle clean shutdown logic
  **Label(s):** graphics, setup

---

### **2. Title:** Draw scrolling starfield background

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Add a parallax-style animated background similar to R-Type.
**List the actions required.:**

Generate stars procedurally or load background textures
Implement horizontal scrolling animation
Ensure scrolling speed uses delta-time
  **Label(s):** graphics, enhancement

---

### **3. Title:** Render player spaceship

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Display the player's ship with its assigned sprite.
**List the actions required.:**

Load player sprite assets
Display the sprite on screen
Apply real-time position updates from the server
  **Label(s):** graphics, game-engine

---

### **4. Title:** Render enemy entities

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Draw enemy ships and obstacles based on server updates.
**List the actions required.:**

Load enemy sprites
Render enemies at server-defined positions
Handle creation and deletion (spawn/despawn)
  **Label(s):** graphics, game-engine

---

### **5. Title:** Render player and enemy missiles

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Display projectiles from both players and enemies.
**List the actions required.:**

Load missile textures
Render missiles with delta-time animation
Remove missiles when notified by server
  **Label(s):** graphics

---

### **6. Title:** Sprite animation support

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Enable frame-based animation in the graphical client.
**List the actions required.:**

Implement sprite sheet support
Add animation component for entities
Manage timing per frame
  **Label(s):** graphics, enhancement, game-engine

---

### **7. Title:** Interpolate entity movement

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Smooth out movement between server updates.
**List the actions required.:**

Store last-known and new entity positions
Implement linear interpolation
Apply interpolation every render frame
  **Label(s):** graphics, enhancement, network

---

### **8. Title:** Display HUD (score, lives, player ID)

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Add on-screen information for the user.
**List the actions required.:**

Render score counter
Render remaining lives
Display player color/identifier
  **Label(s):** graphics, enhancement

---

### **9. Title:** Add explosion and death animations

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Improve visuals when entities are destroyed.
**List the actions required.:**

Load explosion animation frames
Display animation on entity death
Remove entity only after animation completes
  **Label(s):** graphics, enhancement

---

### **10. Title:** Implement delta-time based rendering

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Ensure animations and movement are independent from CPU speed.
**List the actions required.:**

Add clock/time management
Convert movement to time-based
Verify consistent behavior at various framerates
  **Label(s):** graphics, game-engine


### **12. Title:** Implement texture caching & asset manager

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Improve loading performance and memory usage.
**List the actions required.:**

Create a central texture manager
Avoid reloading assets multiple times
Add error handling for missing assets
  **Label(s):** game-engine, enhancement

---

### **13. Title:** Display network debug overlay

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Show useful info for debugging networking issues.
**List the actions required.:**

Add FPS counter
Add ping & packet loss indicators
Toggle overlay with a debug key
  **Label(s):** graphics, tests, network

---

### **14. Title:** Implement GUI for main menu

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Create the entry point of the game experience.
**List the actions required.:**

Draw menu buttons (Play, Quit, Settings)
Handle input and interactions
Transition to gameplay scene
  **Label(s):** graphics, enhancement

---

### **15. Title:** Implement in-game pause menu

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Add a pause menu accessible during gameplay.
**List the actions required.:**

Draw menu overlay
Freeze rendering/gameplay updates
Add “Resume” and “Quit” options
  **Label(s):** graphics, enhancement, game-engine

---

### **16. Title:** Add audio feedback for visuals

**What needs to be accomplished?:**
Synchronize simple sound effects with visuals.
**List the actions required.:**

Play sound on explosion
Play sound when shooting
